<p>again this question but now with code:</p>  <p>I've got a deployed ASP.NET MVC website on an IIS7.5. On one page I've got a fileupload done by a form and inputtype file, submitted to the controller. the controller then redirects me to another view, where an ajax call immediatly fetches some serverside saved information ( JSon for an JSTree). I only have the pdbs for debugging, and I am not allowed to just deploy a new version :/ The problem is: when I call the website from the server itself, there are no worries, everything works fine, the upload and the ajax call. But when I call the website from anywhere else, except the server, I get a 500 internal Server error from the ajax call(debugged with firebug). I tried everything to get a detailed errormessage (edited web.config, set errormessages to detailed in servermanager, etc.), When I attach the VS2013 Debugger to the AppPoolProcess (w3wp.exe) there is no exception thrown when I get the 500-Error.</p>  <p>My Controller is not asynchron.</p>  <p>I copied the content of the physical path and deployed it to another virtual path, there everything works fine. I'm confused :/</p>  <p>Has anyone an idea? :D  The Ajax call in the second view:</p>  <pre><code>    var json; $.ajax({         url: '@Url.Action("BuildTree")',         data: {},         datatype: "json",         async: false,         success: function (data) {             json = data;         },         error: function (data) {             alert("Error: SomeErrorMessage.");         }     });    </code></pre>  <p>The Fileupload in the first view:</p>  <pre><code>@using (Html.BeginForm("UploadAndRedirect", "ControllerName", FormMethod.Post, new { enctype = "multipart/form-data" })) {     @Html.HiddenFor(model =&gt; Model.SomeAttribute)     @Html.HiddenFor(model =&gt; Model.AnotherAttribute)     @Html.TextBoxFor(model =&gt; Model.SelectedFile, new { type = "file" })     @Html.ValidationMessageFor(model =&gt; model.SelectedFile)     @:&lt;input type="submit" name="submit" value="Submit" /&gt;  } </code></pre>  <p>My Controller Upload Method (only very small files, so saving in session is okay):</p>  <pre><code>[HttpPost]     public ActionResult UploadAndRedirect(MyViewModel model)     {         if (ModelState.IsValid)         {             Session["file"] = model.SelectedFile;             return View("TheViewWithTheAjaxCall", model);         }         var Errors = ModelState.Values.SelectMany(v =&gt; v.Errors);          ViewBag.errors = Errors.ElementAt(0).ErrorMessage;         return View("Upload", model);     }  </code></pre>  <p>And finally the method the ajaxcode calls:</p>  <pre><code>public JsonResult BuildTree()     {         String descr = Session["descr"] as String;         String path = GlobalSpecifiedPath + descr + ".extension";         Metadata m = Metadata.FromFile(path);//Lib Function, Lib works on other controller calls.         JsonTreeNode tree = BuildTreeHelper.BuildTree(m);         return Json(tree, JsonRequestBehavior.AllowGet);     } </code></pre>  <p>Okay there is also something strange: when i call the url directly from the browser: <a href="http://myurl/Controller/BuildTree" rel="nofollow">http://myurl/Controller/BuildTree</a> I get the correct Json response, but when i call it after i uploaded a file this also doesn't work, till i call the Method where <code>Session["descr"]</code> is set again.  It seems the <code>Session["descr"]</code> is deleted by the UploadAndRedirect Method but only when it's called from anywhere but the Server?! </p>  <p>The Networktab in Firebug/devtools says the UploadAndRedirect call works (200 ok) The call for BuildTree doesn't work 500 internal server error with no text/xml as response. JQuery works fine.</p>